HEADWORD: Dermoneural
<hw>Der`mo*neu"ral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or in relation with, both dermal and neural
structures; <as>as, the <ex>dermoneural</ex> spines or dorsal fin rays
of fishes</as>.</def> <rj><au>Owen.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

